<a href="/baylymoore">
            <img src="http://b.vimeocdn.com/ps/343/946/3439467_30.jpg" alt="Bayly &amp; Moore" class="portrait portrait_sm">
    </a>

<div class="comment">
    <p class="meta">
        <a href="/baylymoore" class="meta">Bayly &amp; Moore</a> <a tabindex="-1" href="/pro" title="Learn more about Vimeo PRO" data-ga-event-click="button|pro_badge_click|pro"><span class="badge_pro">PRO</span></a> <time datetime="2013-01-06T15:10:18-05:00" title="Sunday, January 6, 2013 3:10 PM" pubdate>1 month ago</time>
            </p>

    
    <div class="text">
                <p class="first">Agreed. It&#039;s been a big few years in frame-by-frame and live-action animation with some fairly significant tech, motion control and software leaps. It&#039;s fairly remarkable that a disicipline/technique that was relegated to niche for the last few decades has steadily made yet another comeback to the point that a large amount of viewers have an understanding of it - fairly rare in film-making techniques.</p>    </div>

    </div>

    </article>
    <article id="comment_8495706" class="article clearfix main comment_8495706">

<a href="/craigseeman">
            <img src="http://b.vimeocdn.com/ps/890/890042_75.jpg" alt="Craig Seeman" class="portrait portrait_lg">
    </a>

<div class="comment">
    <p class="meta">
        <a href="/craigseeman" class="meta">Craig Seeman</a>  <time datetime="2013-01-03T10:54:53-05:00" title="Thursday, January 3, 2013 10:54 AM" pubdate>1 month ago</time>
            </p>

    
    <div class="text">
                <p class="first">I think Apple is paying serious attention to the MacPro replacement. I think most here may not be aware of the challenges involved.</p>
<p>To date there are no Xeon mother boards from Intel with Thunderbolt. To date all Thunderbolt computers have GPUs on the motherboard. If Apple is to release a MacPro replacement with Thunderbolt then Xeon motherboards and independent GPUs must be supported.</p>
<p>I have no doubt Apple is working on both with Intel but that&#039;s likely why we haven&#039;t seen a MacPro replacement yet. Let&#039;s also be clear, it&#039;s not simply Apple but Intel that&#039;s integral to this development.</p>    </div>

    </div>

    </article>
    <article id="comment_8501850" class="article clearfix main comment_8501850">

<a href="/schwartzblack">
            <img src="http://b.vimeocdn.com/ps/462/661/4626615_75.jpg" alt="SCHWARTZ BLACK" class="portrait portrait_lg">
    </a>

